# Cloudflare Pages headers.
# Cross-origin isolation is mandatory for multithreaded WASM (SharedArrayBuffer).
# COEP is `credentialless` (NOT `require-corp`) so the cross-origin Wowhead tooltip
# script + icon CDN load without CORP headers while the page stays isolated.
# Mirrors the Vite dev-server headers in vite.config.ts. See docs/OVERALL_PLAN.md §1/§6.
/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: credentialless

# The vendored ES6 glue (simc.js) is immutable per release tag (the tag is in the
# path). It inherits COOP/COEP from /* above; same-origin assets need no CORP under
# credentialless. The 107 MB simc.wasm is served cross-origin from R2 — see
# docs/DEPLOY.md (R2 custom domain + CORS), not from here.
/engine/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
